Where has the sign-in for My National Trust and My Places gone?
views.desc: <button bound_box=96,1624,984,1776>Where has the sign-in for My National Trust and My</button>

views.text: Due to a major upgrade of our internal systems, My National Trust and the My Places features are no longer available.
Location Services‌
Why does the app ask for my location?
views.signature: [class]android.widget.TextView[resource_id]None[text]Why does the app ask for my location?[enabled,,]

views.text:
The app uses the location provided by your device to show you more useful results, such as places or events near you.

The National Trust does not store or process the location, it is only used within your device.

There are two ways to enable Location Services on your device, one is a general setting and one is an app-specific setting. These vary slightly between devices, so please check the relevant user guide for your device for more details.

For more information about Location Services, we suggest you visit either Apple or Google and browse their terms and conditions.
I don't want to enable location services
views.signature: [class]android.widget.TextView[resource_id]None[text]I don't want to enable location services[enabled,,]

views.text: That's absolutely fine, you can still use all the features of the app and can search by town, county or postcode to find NT places. You'll see a list of places by A-Z on the Discover screen instead places nearby.
Mobile Data
Does the app use my mobile data connection?
views.signature: [class]android.widget.TextView[resource_id]None[text]Does the app use my mobile data connection?[enabled,,]

views.text: If your device is connected to the internet using 3G/4G or Wi-Fi it will use mobile data to download information and images whilst the app is in use.
Can I use the app offline?

The app will work offline but certain features will not be available as they require an internet connection: 

Google Maps

Events information
When is the information in the app updated?
views.signature: [class]android.widget.TextView[resource_id]None[text]When is the information in the app updated?[enabled,,]

views.text:
The app checks our central systems periodically for new data, this includes: 

Places

Opening times

Prices

Directions

There is a date/time shown on each place page to indicate the last time the information was checked.
Events
How do I get reminders about Events?
views.signature: [class]android.widget.TextView[resource_id]None[text]How do I get reminders about Events?[enabled,,]

views.text: On the event details page, use the 'Add to your calendar' button to create a reminder about the event in your device's calendar.
Maps
How do I download a map of the property/estate/garden?

Once you've used the app to find a place to visit (e.g. Stourhead), open the place page and scroll down to the 'Maps' section. Tap on a map to download a PDF version to your device.

Please note: not all places have maps available at present.
How do I remove downloaded maps from my device?
views.signature: [class]android.widget.TextView[resource_id]None[text]How do I remove downloaded maps from my device?[enabled,,]

views.text: Go to My Files (Samsung) or Files > Downloads > National Trust and delete the folder or an individual PDF as required.
Which other types of content can I download?
views.signature: [class]android.widget.TextView[resource_id]None[text]Which other types of content can I download?[enabled,,]

views.text: Audio files, trail content and maps are available to download in the app. The type and availability of content varies on each place page.
